THE GREENBRIER CLASSIC
July 6, 2014
Angel Cabrera
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT







Q.   Your first PGA win on American soil.   What does it mean to win here at the Greenbrier?
ANGEL CABRERA:   This is very important.   All tournaments are important.   PGA events are very important, and I'm very happy.

Q.   When you had the eagle and the three‑stroke lead, a couple hiccups down the stretch.   Tell me about them. 
ANGEL CABRERA:   After the eagle, I still hit good shots.   I hit a good shot on 14.   It came back off the green.   Hit a good shot on 15, it rolled into the rough, but I just kept hitting good shots.

Q.   When you saw a 61 earlier in the day by McNeill, were you a little worried going into the first tee that you needed to put up a good number today?
ANGEL CABRERA:   Obviously, I knew I had to do things right, you know, keep on playing.   That's all I could do.

Q.   Angel, you said this place reminded you of home, Argentina.   Talk about that.   You said these hills. 
ANGEL CABRERA:   Yeah, the mountains and the rivers and the lakes and all that remind myself of where I grew up, in CÃ³rdoba. 

Q.   (Inaudible)?
ANGEL CABRERA:   Going to Houston to work a little and then Friday I go to Scotland.

Q.   Is it safe to say you'll be back here for many years to come?
ANGEL CABRERA:   Oh, yeah, if they permit me to come back, I'll be here. 







END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT